  <details class="artifact-section accordion-section">
    <summary class="accordion-title">Skills</summary>
    <div class="accordion-content">
      <p>Skills are specialized capabilities that extend AI assistants like Claude Code with domain-specific knowledge, workflows, and behaviors. They define how the assistant should respond to specific types of tasks, including what tools it can use and what process it should follow.</p>
      <p class="file-location"><strong>File Location Example:</strong> <code>[category]/skills/[skill-name].md</code> (e.g., <code>content-strategy/skills/humanizer.md</code>)</p>
      <p>Skills are invoked using slash commands (e.g., <code>/humanizer</code>) and can include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Name and description:</strong> How to invoke the skill and when to use it</li>
        <li><strong>Allowed tools:</strong> Which tools the skill can access (Read, Write, Edit, etc.)</li>
        <li><strong>Process steps:</strong> The workflow the AI should follow</li>
        <li><strong>Pattern recognition:</strong> Specific items to look for or transform</li>
        <li><strong>Output format:</strong> How results should be presented</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="example-block">
        <div class="example-label">Example: Code Review Skill</div>
        <code>---
name: code-review
description: |
  Review code for quality, security, and best practices.
  Use when asked to review pull requests or code changes.
allowed-tools:
  - Read
  - Grep
  - Glob
---

# Code Review Skill

You are a code reviewer focused on quality, security, and maintainability.

## Your Task

When given code to review:
1. **Read the code** - Understand the changes and context
2. **Check for issues** - Security vulnerabilities, bugs, edge cases
3. **Evaluate quality** - Naming, structure, readability
4. **Suggest improvements** - Offer actionable recommendations

## Review Checklist
- [ ] No hardcoded secrets or credentials
- [ ] Error handling covers edge cases
- [ ] Functions have clear, single responsibilities
- [ ] Variable names are descriptive
- [ ] No commented-out code left behind

## Output Format
Provide:
1. Summary of what the code does
2. List of issues found (if any)
3. Specific suggestions for improvement</code>
